    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A colorless liquid solvent compound of five isomers in the form of a volatile liquid with the smell and taste of bananas. Introduced in 1888 as a solvent for cellulose nitrate and later used for cellulose acetate. Applications include dyeing and finishing textiles, floor coverings, as flavoring, in polishes, varnishes, and metallic paints.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>由五種同質異構物組成的無色液態溶劑，具揮發性，聞或吃起來有香蕉味道；此物質於1888年問世，原本作為硝酸纖維素之溶劑，之後則用於醋酸纖維素；其用途包括紡織品及地板鋪物之染色與上光，也可添加於拋光劑、清漆以及金屬塗料中以製造香味。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
